               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490611-name-329" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-329" type="surname" value="FLOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-329" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY FLOWER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in partnership with Arnold Flower—I have a contract for constructing a dam at the Houses of Parliament—the prisoner vas employed there two months—he was found with some iron plates, which I claim.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. HORRY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Has any other person got a contract but you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not there—we very seldom have any of these plates drop into the water—if they do, we find them again when the barge is unloaded—they might sometimes be thrown up with the mud for ballast.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18490611-name-330" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-330" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-330" type="surname" value="MILLERMAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18490611-name-330" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM MILLERMAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, B</hi> 95). On 24th May I followed the prisoner over Westminster-bridge—he was carrying a basket, which appeared heavy—I stopped him, and found these two iron plates in it—he said he found them in a barge, and offered me 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. to let him go—I got this plate (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) from the firm—it exactly matches with these.</p>
               <p>
